# Markdown documentation files
*.md
# Root *.md is ignored by default with a curated allowlist below.
# CLAUDE.md is the repo's engineering contract for agents and humans (it points
# at LOOPS.md); both are team documentation, not personal scratch, so they are
# allowlisted. Revert these two lines if the intent was to keep them local —
# note that CLAUDE.md must live at the repo root to be picked up automatically,
# so it cannot simply move under docs/.
!CLAUDE.md
!LOOPS.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!DEV_GUIDE.md
!docs/**/*.md
# release-notes/ is the per-version human release note that `ship it` writes.
# Without this line `*.md` above swallows it AT ANY DEPTH and the notes are
# silently untracked — the whole point of them is that they ship.
!release-notes/**/*.md
# Session handoff. Same trap as release-notes above: `*.md` matches at any
# depth, and a handoff that does not survive the session is worthless.
!handoff.md
# The impeccable skill is installed project-scoped so it travels with the repo,
# and it IS its markdown: SKILL.md is the entry point and reference/<command>.md
# defines each command's flow. `*.md` above matches at any depth, so without this
# line a clone gets the 63 .mjs scripts and none of the 33 files that make them
# mean anything — an install that is present, broken, and silent about it.
!.claude/skills/impeccable/**/*.md
!todo.md
!README.md
# The old-idiom -> new-idiom map for the vanilla binding (LOOPS XXXVI: "write the
# mapping down"). It is what keeps three bindings agreeing on one API instead of
# drifting, so it is team documentation in the same sense as LOOPS.md — and the
# `*.md` rule above would swallow it exactly the way it nearly swallowed the
# release notes.
!PORTING.md
# The generated guide an LLM coding agent reads to consume zen-ui. One at the
# repo root plus one per package (published in each package's `files`). Same
# `*.md`-at-any-depth trap as release-notes: without these, the per-package
# copies never ship and a consumer's agent finds nothing in node_modules.
!AGENTS.md
!packages/**/AGENTS.md
*.txt
components-list.txt
components-list.csv


vite.config.http.ts

# npm configuration (contains tokens)
.npmrc
.visual/

# Built by ./deploy.sh — the whole site (landing + both demos) as one static tree.
dist-site/

# scratch dirs from scripts/check-bundle-size.mjs (must live in-repo for
# node to resolve vite plugins; removed on exit, ignored in case of a crash)
.zen-size-*/

# Demo catalogue thumbnails — generated by `bun run gen:previews`, several MB of
# binary that would be rewritten wholesale on every regeneration. deploy.sh
# regenerates them so the published site always has them, and the cards degrade
# to text when a file is missing.
packages/*/public/previews/
